mappeR is a topological visualisation algorithm, initially described in
Topological Methods for the Analysis of High Dimensional Data Sets and 3D Object Recognition 
Singh, G., Memoli, F., Carlsson, G. (2007)

It requires igraph, fastcluster, MASS and mclust.

Install from folder (on Windows)

# check the package source and documentation
"path\to\R.exe" CMD check mappeR

# build the source package
"path\to\R.exe" CMD build --binary mappeR

# build a windows zip
"path\to\R.exe" INSTALL --build mappeR

Alternatively, use Hadley Wickham's devtools package 

require(devtools)
install_github("arnhew99/mappeR")